temporal pbmc overlap

yo jaccard ignores proportions/clones, just based off cdr3s

Not really any dramatic differences after filtering out the cell types with very few cells Tregs have very low overlap in general, Th2 as well, whereas CD8s have much higher

Once again, not really strong clinical diffs, maybe lynch higher CD8 act? (which is surprising) and nlr higher CD4 act? then again this is peripheral so not sure what to expect Treg has comparable temporal overlap to naive populations - less large preserved clones?

all really low counts, but CD8 Activated actually does look lower overlap in nlr though

the questionable data shows enrichment towards both extremes with outliers removed though, it looks like just increase in TM overlap for NLR

it kinda looked like something was there, but looks inconclusive
